author: ehildenb
content: Well gosh darn, it worked! It shows the second loop (the actual for-loop I wrote) 3 times because it took two iterations of the first loop (the abi decoding) to find out that it was indeed a loop. So the first copy of the last loop is "if there were no iterations of the first loop", the second one is "if there was one iteration of the first loop", and the last one is "if there were N>1 iterations of the first loop".
